<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1266,1509]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1410,1436]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Comments:</emphasis>
Most records of this species are under the specific epithet 
<emphasis box="[1021,1093,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">piceus</emphasis>
Dallas, either in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant &amp; Rey" authorityYear="1866" box="[1295,1404,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Peribalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1295,1404,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Peribalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1860" box="[151,297,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Holcostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,297,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Holcostethus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and this is the name it was catalogued under by 
<bibRefCitation author="Froeschner, R. C." box="[854,1064,1447,1473]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="544 - 607" refId="ref49613" refString="Froeschner, R. C. (1988) Family Pentatomidae Leach, 1815. The stink bugs. In: Henry, T. J. &amp; Froeschner, R. C. (Eds.), Catalog of the Heteroptera, or True Bugs, of Canada and the Continental United States. E. J. Brill, Leiden, New York, pp. 544 - 607. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / 9781351070447 - 30" type="book chapter" year="1988">Froeschner (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rider, D. A. &amp; Rolston, L. H." box="[1075,1343,1446,1473]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="845 - 855" refId="ref59865" refString="Rider, D. A. &amp; Rolston, L. H. (1995) Nomenclatural changes in the Pentatomidae (Hemiptera-Heteroptera). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 97 (4), 845 - 855." type="journal article" year="1995">Rider &amp; Rolston (1995)</bibRefCitation>
showed that Dallas’ name was preoccupied and proposed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rider &amp; Rolston" authorityYear="1995" box="[705,990,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Holcostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macdonaldi">
<emphasis box="[705,990,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Holcostethus macdonaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement name.
</paragraph>
